caption.text:
So I got an announcement for this plan I’ve had for October. The YouTube channel, Tats TopVideos, made a video about their top 85 freeware horror games, as seen in the screenshot posted here. So what I’ve decided to do is that everyday starting tomorrow is that I’ll be covering games 31-1 and giving my own opinions on them. Seeing as this is basically opinions on opinions, chances are you’ll disagree about some of these games being the best of the indie horror genre. Also I covered only about a 1/3rd of the games mentioned so feel free to check out the whole video via the link in my profile. It’s an experiment but I hope you guys will enjoy and you’ll see some good games and some mediocre games and possibly me throwing beef at people who don’t know I exist. Lastly there were several games that ranked above the 31 point that I felt deserved a higher ranking and on Halloween I’ll be doing mini-reviews of those games as sort of an honorable–should’ve been higher–mention.

#Gamefemerides
Hace 25 años es lanzado DOOM II. Es un juego de disparos en primera persona, el segundo título de id Software de la franquicia @doom . Fue originalmente lanzado para computadoras MS-DOS en 1994, y para Mactintosh en 1995. A diferencia de Doom, que solo estuvo disponible como shareware y por correo, Doom II fue un lanzamiento comercial en tiendas. Master Levels for Doom II, un paquete de expansión que incluye 21 nuevos niveles, fue lanzado el 26 de diciembre de 1995 por id Software. 
Debido a su éxito y popularidad, Doom II fue luego lanzado para Game Boy Advance de Nintendo en 2002, Xbox Live Arcade en 2010, y para @Nintendo Switch, @PlayStation 4, y @Xbox One en 2019. La liberación del código fuente del Doom original ha participado que se portee a otras plataformas.

When I start feeling better I'll get you guys a better picture along with game play footage, but for now this crappy picture from my phone will have to suffice. Sorry!

If you haven't played #CodeVein yet you definitely should. When I heard it was going to basically be the anime version of Dark Souls I didn't have high hopes... Boy was I mistaken. This games customization is probably one of my all time favorites because of how vastly different each character can be, and the game play is amazing. 
I will say that in multiplayer if you have to leave and come back to a revnants map too often it will start to bug, at least in a couple of the maps so be careful. This but will make you unable to move and often make your character invisible and useless, at which point you'll have to leave and rejoin again. If you have a boss fight coming up make sure the host waits for you to get to the mist barrier before starting the encounter so you can get in. There's also a bug that will stop you from interacting with anything with a menu at the home base aside from the mistle, at which point try restarting your client or system. 
For a new game, these bugs are pretty minor. 
All in all, this game has easily made it into my top 3 favorites and you should definitely give it a shot!

Let's plays of this game will be posted to my #youtube channel once I start feeling a little better. Thanks for your patience 🧡🖤🧡 #newyoutuber #gamergirl #gamer #quickreview #newgame  #codeveinreview #games #gaming #pc #ps4

caption.text:
Did you know that when #TiedIn first started we kicked off with an episode about #AttackOnTitan? It’s true, we did and if you missed it and wanna know what all of the fuss is then here’s a nice clip from our debut episode!

I think we’ve come quite far in only a few months of making content, even if it’s just smaller details like getting our episodes more compact, learning what jokes to get rid of and what to keep. Getting our audio more consistent for levels, getting rid of background noise and even things like animated graphics, the intro video package and outro greenscreen quality.

I’m proud of the content we’re making now but even though it’s a little rough around the edges I enjoy the content we started with too. Anyway, I digress.

Here is our first Tied-In YouTube video if you missed it. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=z8H_Yd2HlNQ

preview_comments.text: The Konami of old is long gone. They shifted their strategy to mobile a while back last I heard. Was around the same time the whole Kojima nonsense was going on with them. I take everything they release now with a grain of salt and expect the worst unless proven otherwise. Unfortunately they hold the key to a lot of famous franchises.

caption.text: A little gaming related news post, some may already know but the new Castlevania game coming out is supposedly going to be a mobile phone game only? First we get a not so good version of the latest Contra just being released and now a franchise that a lot of people like not to mention own consoles for we get Castlevania on a mobile phone game? Not opposed to playing a game on my phone but really Konami what audience are you trying to attract? Really feel like Konami is letting us down yet again with some of these beloved franchises. I don’t know what else to say can’t believe no Castlevania games for the current gen consoles I mean I liked Bloodstained but another one to add to the mix would have been great I mean hell this could really be a great game but that’s just me being cynical. Let’s just say I’m shaking my head.. #gamer #gaming #gamingnews
